addrelease.author: Frederik "Freso" S. Olesen, Lukáš Lalinský, Philip Jägenstedt
addrelease.description: Adds a plugin context menu option to clusters and single files to help you quickly add them as releases or standalone recordings to the MusicBrainz database via the website by pre-populating artists, track names and times.
addrelease.name: Add Cluster As Release

albumartist_website.author: Sophist
albumartist_website.description: Add's the album artist(s) Official Homepage(s)(if they are defined in the MusicBrainz database).
albumartist_website.name: Album Artist Website

classicdiscnumber.author: Lukas Lalinsky
classicdiscnumber.description: Moves disc numbers and subtitles from the separate tags to album titles.
classicdiscnumber.name: Classic Disc Numbers

cuesheet.author: Lukáš Lalinský
cuesheet.description: Generate cuesheet (.cue file) from an album.
cuesheet.name: Generate Cuesheet

discnumber.author: Lukas Lalinsky
discnumber.description:
Moves disc numbers and subtitles from album titles to separate tags. For example:
"Aerial (disc 1: A Sea of Honey)"
  • album = "Aerial"
  • discnumber = "1"
  • discsubtitle = "A Sea of Honey"
discnumber.name: Disc Numbers

featartist.author: Lukas Lalinsky, Bryan Toth
featartist.description: Removes feat. artists from track titles.  Substitution is case insensitive.
featartist.name: Feat. Artists Removed

featartistsintitles.author: Lukas Lalinsky, Michael Wiencek, Bryan Toth
featartistsintitles.description: Move "feat." from artist names to album and track titles. Match is case insensitive.
featartistsintitles.name: Feat. Artists in Titles

lastfm.author: Lukáš Lalinský
lastfm.description: Use tags from Last.fm as genre.
lastfm.name: Last.fm

lastfmplus.author: RifRaf, Lukáš Lalinský, voiceinsideyou
lastfmplus.description:
Uses folksonomy tags from Last.fm to
* Sort music into major and minor genres based on configurable genre "whitelists"
* Add "mood", "occasion" and other custom categories
* Add "original release year" and "decade" tags, as well as populate blank dates.
lastfmplus.name: Last.fm.Plus

no_release.author: Johannes Weißl
no_release.description: Do not store specific release information in releases of unknown origin.
no_release.name: No release

release_type.author: Elliot Chance
release_type.description: Appends information to EPs and Singles
release_type.name: Release Type

replaygain.author: Philipp Wolfer
replaygain.description: Calculate ReplayGain for selected files and albums.
replaygain.name: ReplayGain

sort_multivalue_tags.author: Sophist
sort_multivalue_tags.description: Sort Multi-Value Tags e.g. Release Type, Lyrics alphabetically.
sort_multivalue_tags.name: Sort Multi-Value Tags

standardise_performers.author: Sophist
standardise_performers.description:
Splits multi-instrument performer tags into singleinstruments and combines names so e.g. (from 10cc by 10cc track 1):
Performer [acoustic guitar, bass, dobro, electric guitar and tambourine]: Graham GouldmanPerformer [acoustic guitar, electric guitar, grand piano and synthesizer]: Lol CremePerformer [electric guitar, moog and slide guitar]: Eric Stewart
becomes:
Performer [acoustic guitar]: Graham Gouldman; Lol CremePerformer [bass]: Graham GouldmanPerformer [dobro]: Graham GouldmanPerformer [electric guitar]: Eric Stewart; Graham Gouldman; Lol CremePerformer [grand piano]: Lol CremePerformer [moog]: Eric StewartPerformer [slide guitar]: Eric StewartPerformer [synthesizer]: Lol CremePerformer [tambourine]: Graham Gouldman
standardise_performers.name: Standardise Performers

titlecase.author: Javier Kohen
titlecase.description: Capitalize First Character In Every Word Of A Title
titlecase.name: Title Case

tracks2clipboard.author: Michael Elsdörfer
tracks2clipboard.description: Exports a cluster's tracks to the clipboard, so it can be copied into the tracklist field on MusicBrainz
tracks2clipboard.name: Copy Cluster to Clipboard

viewvariables.author: Sophist
viewvariables.description: Display a dialog box listing the metadata variables for the track / file.
viewvariables.name: View script variables
